# Ralph Loop per-story agent prompt template.
#
# Variables (set as shell env vars before calling envsubst):
#   MILESTONE_ID      e.g. M77
#   STORY_ID          e.g. M77-02
#   STORY_TITLE       the story title
#   TEST_TARGET       the story's test_target (Java class)
#   PHASE_REF         line reference in the source plan
#   ACCEPT_BLOCK      newline-separated acceptance bullets
#   SKILLS_BLOCK      newline-separated skill names
#   FILES_BLOCK       newline-separated files this story touches
#   STORIES_FILE      absolute path to M{NN}-stories.json
#   REPO_ROOT         absolute path to repo root
#
# Invocation:  envsubst < .agents/templates/M{NN}-prompt.md.template
# Or via:      scripts/ralph/render_prompt.sh $STORY_ID

# Ralph Loop — ${MILESTONE_ID} / ${STORY_ID}

You are an autonomous coding agent working on the MedExpertMatch repo at `${REPO_ROOT}`.

## Story

- **Milestone:** ${MILESTONE_ID}
- **Story ID:** ${STORY_ID}
- **Title:** ${STORY_TITLE}
- **Phase reference:** ${PHASE_REF}
- **Test target:** `${TEST_TARGET}` (run with `mvn test -Dtest='${TEST_TARGET}'` for unit, `mvn verify -Dit.test='${TEST_TARGET}'` for IT)
- **Stories file:** `${STORIES_FILE}`

## Skills to load (mandatory — read each SKILL.md before changing code)

${SKILLS_BLOCK}

## Files this story touches (additive — do not touch files outside this list unless strictly required by the test)

${FILES_BLOCK}

## Acceptance criteria (the story is "done" when all of these are true)

${ACCEPT_BLOCK}

## How to work

1. Read `${REPO_ROOT}/.agents/plans/progress.txt` for cross-iteration learnings from prior stories.
2. Read every skill listed above (in full) from `${REPO_ROOT}/.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`.
3. Read `${REPO_ROOT}/.agents/plans/M${MILESTONE_ID#M}-*.md` (the source plan) for the full milestone context.
4. Implement the change. Do not edit the `M${MILESTONE_ID#M}-stories.json` file — `scripts/ralph.sh` does that after the test passes.
5. Run the test target. If it fails, fix and re-run. Iterate until green.
6. When the test target is green, return the unified diff of your changes in EXACTLY this format:

\`\`\`diff
--- a/<path>
+++ b/<path>
@@ -<old-range> +<new-range> @@
 <old-line>
-<removed>
+<added>
 \`\`\`

The diff MUST apply cleanly with `git apply --check` from `${REPO_ROOT}`. Include all files you created or modified. Do not include any prose outside the \`\`\`diff fenced block.

## Hard rules (AGENTS.md global boundaries)

- NEVER add `Co-authored-by:` trailers to commits — but you are not committing in this story, `scripts/ralph.sh` will commit.
- NEVER introduce code that exposes patient data (PHI) in any form.
- NEVER modify `pom.xml` dependency versions.
- NEVER add new Flyway migrations on V2+ — only V1 consolidations.
- NEVER swap the AI provider away from OpenAI-compatible endpoints.
- NEVER delete or archive modules or domain entities.
- Stay within the files listed above. If you need to touch a file not in the list, prefer the minimum-diff approach: extend an existing helper, do not create a new abstraction.

## Return format reminder

The very last thing you output must be a single \`\`\`diff fenced block. Nothing else.
